  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "At the moment we `assert` that proofs of possession are correct:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    assert bls_verify(\r\n        pubkey=deposit_input.pubkey,\r\n        message_hash=signed_root(deposit_input, \"proof_of_possession\"),\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis `assert` is bad for a few reasons:\r\n\r\n1) The \"logic to ensure that deposits from 1.0 chain are processed in order\" may prevent \"skipping\" deposits.\r\n2) User funds go in a black hole.\r\n\r\nMy suggestion would be to process the deposit (no `assert`) and make validator status go directly to \"withdrawn\".",
