    "body": "We already handled (1) in master. Looks like a cleanup messed up the functionality.\r\n\r\nSee [`process_deposit` in master](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#process_deposit). We do the following to keep processing moving forward even if the validation failed.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nif not proof_is_valid:\r\n    return\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs for (2), I'm more amenable to black holes than you are :)\r\nIs there any security risk in moving the user funds to withdrawable if they failed their PoP? ",
